Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

Ischaemum rugosum

Photo by International Rice Research Institute (IRRI), licensed under CC BY 2.0

The assembly is haploid, and the genome is diploid. It has a haploid genome size of 700 Mb, and has 10 haploid chromosomes.

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Ischaemum rugosum from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Figure 1 from the main text, with Ischaemum rugosum highlighted with colored points.

Highlighted Figure 2

Figure 2 from the main text, with Ischaemum rugosum highlighted with colored points.

Dotplot of Ischaemum rugosum vs. Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Ischaemum rugosum along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Ischaemum rugosum is a diploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 1 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Ischaemum rugosum

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Ischaemum rugosum along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Ischaemum rugosum is a diploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 1 lines, one for each subgenome.
